Note on the `...` button and ContextMenu interaction: Radix ContextMenu does not support programmatic `open` via a button click. The spec's Open Question #2 notes this. For v1, the `...` button can use a parallel `DropdownMenu` with the same items, or simply trigger the context menu. The simplest approach for v1 is to have the `...` button use a `DropdownMenu`:

```tsx
import { DropdownMenu, DropdownMenuTrigger, DropdownMenuContent, DropdownMenuItem, DropdownMenuSeparator } from '@/layers/shared/ui';

// Replace the simple SidebarMenuAction with:
<DropdownMenu>
  <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>
    <SidebarMenuAction
      showOnHover={!isMobile}
      aria-label="Agent actions"
      onClick={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}
    >
      <MoreHorizontal className="size-4" />
    </SidebarMenuAction>
  </DropdownMenuTrigger>
  <DropdownMenuContent side="right" align="start" className="w-48">
    <DropdownMenuItem onClick={onTogglePin}>
      {isPinned ? <><PinOff className="mr-2 size-4" />Unpin agent</> : <><Pin className="mr-2 size-4" />Pin agent</>}
    </DropdownMenuItem>
    <DropdownMenuSeparator />
    <DropdownMenuItem onClick={onManage}>
      <ListTree className="mr-2 size-4" />Manage agent
    </DropdownMenuItem>
    <DropdownMenuItem onClick={onEditSettings}>
      <Settings className="mr-2 size-4" />Edit settings
    </DropdownMenuItem>
    <DropdownMenuSeparator />
    <DropdownMenuItem onClick={onNewSession}>
      <Plus className="mr-2 size-4" />New session
    </DropdownMenuItem>
  </DropdownMenuContent>
</DropdownMenu>
```

